fields.name: s1mple
fields.bio: Oleksandr “s1mple” Kostyliev was born on October 2, 1997 and is currently playing for BC.Game as an AWPer. s1mple is considered by many to be the best Counter-Strike player of all time, a claim that is supported by his many achievements and trophies. His teams have won a Major, an Intel Grand Slam, and many top tier tournaments, while his personal accolades include over 20 HLTV MVP medals, and the number one position in HLTV’s ‘best player of the year’ lists. He was the runner-up in 2019 and 2020.

He has won multiple MVP awards, and has come close to winning HLTV’s best player of the year award (coming in third in 2021 and 2018, and second in 2017).

fields.name: XANTARES
fields.bio: İsmailсan “XANTARES” Dörtkardeş is a Turkish professional Counter-Strike 2 player, and is currently playing for Aurora as a rifler. XANTARES is a very popular player, in part due to the fact that he has the ‘XANTARES peek’ named after him. This is a way of peeking where a player wide peeks (thus moving past the angle that an enemy might be holding) and then shoots the enemy almost instantly due to near perfect crosshair placement.

He was signed by G2 Esports in June of 2021.
